parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion can cause brake failure, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pedal pressure
brake pedal travels to the floor
failure to slow down when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause brake failure, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Early brake pad wear can lead to premature rotor damage, increased stopping distances, and reduced vehicle safety.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when brakes are applied
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel
brake pads wear out quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause loss of traction, increased stopping distances, and reduced vehicle safety.
symptoms: Clicking or grinding noises when brakes are applied
ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
brakes do not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off while in operation, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause smoke to fill the interior of the vehicle, creating a hazardous environment.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while in operation
smoke comes from the front driver side door panel
the vehicle's lights (headlights
taillights
console lights) fail or blow frequently
the horn fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the voltage regulator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to frequent blown lights, faulty horn operation, and other electrical issues.
symptoms: Frequent blown headlights
taillights
and other lights
faulty horn operation
electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to accidents or near-misses, as the driver is unable to alert other drivers or pedestrians of their presence.
symptoms: The horn fails to function properly
excessive force is needed to activate the horn
the horn does not work at times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and turbo failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power steering
the engine emits heavy black smoke from the exhaust system
the engine emits white smoke from the front and rear of the car
the turbo fails
and the engine needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high idling engine can cause the vehicle to vibrate excessively, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: The engine idles high
the RPM surges frequently
and the check engine light comes on periodically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of coil springs can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, damage to surrounding components, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Coil springs break or fracture
causing damage to tires
wheels
or other suspension components; uneven vehicle ride; clunking or knocking noises while driving; pulling or drifting to one side while driving.
